  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Novice Dungeon Master</strong> is a turn-based strategy simulation management game.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >It's a game where the protagonist, who used to explore beginner dungeons, becomes the master of a dungeon due to a contract and manages the dungeon for 30 days, set in a fantasy world with dungeons, adventures, monsters, and guilds.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Various types of adventurers visit the dungeon.</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/store_npc.PNG?t=1769476735\" /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >And they visit the dungeon for different purposes.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Herbs and minerals, battles and treasures, dreams and hopes... </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Anything is possible in the dungeon.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >So how do you send them back?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >There are various methods. For example,</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >you can place facilities they desire...</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/83f1d7b87b586934a01bb721dff974ae.poster.avif?t=1769476735\" width=410 height=318 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/83f1d7b87b586934a01bb721dff974ae.webm?t=1769476735\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/83f1d7b87b586934a01bb721dff974ae.mp4?t=1769476735\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Or set up traps...</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/6708923ee5da93c62cfdf45cbefe1591.poster.avif?t=1769476735\" width=164 height=108 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/6708923ee5da93c62cfdf45cbefe1591.webm?t=1769476735\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Or you can place monsters.</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/5cc5b403ebac31c6bb58660cd5c3aba1.poster.avif?t=1769476735\" width=760 height=584 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/5cc5b403ebac31c6bb58660cd5c3aba1.webm?t=1769476735\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >If they are satisfied in the dungeon, word will spread and the dungeon's popularity will increase, which means more adventurers will come!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >If they face danger in the dungeon, word will get out that the dungeon is dangerous, but that also becomes a reason for adventurers to visit.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >However, if they fail to obtain what they want, they will leave disappointed.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This will directly lead to a decline in the dungeon's popularity.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You must try to prevent this from happening. Because according to the contract, you must <strong>defend the dungeon</strong> while also <strong>increasing its rank!</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >No matter what method you use, just grow and defend the dungeon!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >If you safely complete the 30-day contract...</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/a248334e75c7bdfbac2ffd0cf19c4ef8.avif?t=1769476735\" width=576 height=192 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >An ending based on your actions will await you!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Head into the dungeon to find out what ending awaits you!</p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Novice Dungeon Master</strong> is a turn-based strategy simulation management game.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >It's a game where the protagonist, who used to explore beginner dungeons, becomes the master of a dungeon due to a contract and manages the dungeon for 30 days, set in a fantasy world with dungeons, adventures, monsters, and guilds.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Various types of adventurers visit the dungeon.</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/store_npc.PNG?t=1769476735\" /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >And they visit the dungeon for different purposes.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Herbs and minerals, battles and treasures, dreams and hopes... </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Anything is possible in the dungeon.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >So how do you send them back?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >There are various methods. For example,</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >you can place facilities they desire...</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/83f1d7b87b586934a01bb721dff974ae.poster.avif?t=1769476735\" width=410 height=318 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/83f1d7b87b586934a01bb721dff974ae.webm?t=1769476735\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/83f1d7b87b586934a01bb721dff974ae.mp4?t=1769476735\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Or set up traps...</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/6708923ee5da93c62cfdf45cbefe1591.poster.avif?t=1769476735\" width=164 height=108 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/6708923ee5da93c62cfdf45cbefe1591.webm?t=1769476735\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Or you can place monsters.</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/5cc5b403ebac31c6bb58660cd5c3aba1.poster.avif?t=1769476735\" width=760 height=584 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/5cc5b403ebac31c6bb58660cd5c3aba1.webm?t=1769476735\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >If they are satisfied in the dungeon, word will spread and the dungeon's popularity will increase, which means more adventurers will come!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >If they face danger in the dungeon, word will get out that the dungeon is dangerous, but that also becomes a reason for adventurers to visit.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >However, if they fail to obtain what they want, they will leave disappointed.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This will directly lead to a decline in the dungeon's popularity.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You must try to prevent this from happening. Because according to the contract, you must <strong>defend the dungeon</strong> while also <strong>increasing its rank!</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >No matter what method you use, just grow and defend the dungeon!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >If you safely complete the 30-day contract...</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2886090/extras/a248334e75c7bdfbac2ffd0cf19c4ef8.avif?t=1769476735\" width=576 height=192 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >An ending based on your actions will await you!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Head into the dungeon to find out what ending awaits you!</p>",
